N2  - In this paper, we outline (i) why σ-convergence may not accompany ?-convergence, (ii) discuss evidence of ?-convergence in the United States, and (iii) use U.S. county-level data containing over 3,000 cross-sectional observations to demonstrate that σ-convergence cannot be detected at the county level across the United States, or within the large majority of the individual U.S. states considered separately. Indeed, in many cases statistically significant σ-divergence is found.
ER  - 

